GrooZo – Terms & Conditions
Last Updated: 04-12-2025
Welcome to GrooZo, a food-delivery platform connecting users with local restaurants and food outlets. By downloading, accessing, or using the GrooZo mobile application (“App”), you agree to the following Terms & Conditions. Please read them carefully.

1. Acceptance of Terms
  By using GrooZo, you acknowledge that:
  - You have read, understood, and agree to be bound by these Terms & Conditions.
  - You are at least 18 years old or using the App under parental/guardian supervision.
  - GrooZo may update these terms at any time, and continued use of the App means you accept the changes.

2. Nature of Service
  GrooZo provides:
  - A platform to browse menus from partner restaurants.
  - The ability to place food delivery or takeaway orders.
  - Real-time order tracking.
  - Customer support for order-related issues.
  GrooZo does not own any restaurant listed on the platform. Each restaurant is solely responsible for: 
  - Food preparation
  - Food quality 
  - Packaging
  - Timely handover to delivery partners

3. User Account & Responsibilities
  To use GrooZo, you must create an account using valid personal information. You agree to:
  - Provide accurate details (name, phone number, address, etc.).
  - Maintain the confidentiality of your OTPs and login details.
  - Not create multiple or fake accounts.
  - Not misuse, hack, or attempt unauthorized access to the App.
  - GrooZo may suspend or terminate accounts if suspicious or fraudulent activity is detected.

4. Ordering, Payment & Pricing
  4.1 Ordering
    - Once an order is placed, it is immediately sent to the restaurant.
    - Cancellation may not be possible after preparation starts.
   
  4.2 Pricing
    - Prices displayed are set by restaurants.
    - Taxes and delivery charges may be applicable.
    - GrooZo reserves the right to modify delivery charges at any time.
    
  4.3 Payment
    GrooZo supports:
    - Online payments (UPI, cards, net banking, wallets),
    - Cash on Delivery (if enabled).
    
    In case of payment failure:
    - The amount will be automatically refunded within the standard banking time.
  
5. Delivery
  GrooZo strives for timely delivery but does not guarantee:
  - Delivery times,
  - Availability of delivery partners,
  - Delivery in extreme weather or restricted areas.
  - Once food is picked up from the restaurant, the delivery partner is responsible for transit.

6. Cancellation & Refund Policy
  6.1 Order Cancellation
    - Orders may be cancelled if:
    - The restaurant is unable to accept the order,
    - Items are unavailable,
    - There is a technical issue,
    - You cancel before preparation begins (subject to feasibility).
    
  6.2 Refunds
    Refunds are issued when:
    - Orders are cancelled by the restaurant or GrooZo,
    - You paid online and cancellation is eligible,
    - Delivery issues are verified by GrooZo.
    Refund Mode:
    - Online payment → Refund to original mode
    - COD → No monetary refund applicable
    Refund Time:
    - Usually 3–7 working days (bank dependent).
  
7. Food Quality & Allergies
  Restaurants are solely responsible for:
  - Food taste,
  - Quality,
  - Hygiene,
  - Freshness.
    
  You must check the item description, ingredients, and allergy information before ordering.
  GrooZo is not liable for any food-related health issues.

8. Offers, Discounts & Promotions
  - GrooZo may offer promo codes, discounts, or loyalty points from time to time.
  - Offers may change or be withdrawn without prior notice.
  - Offers cannot be combined unless specifically allowed.
  - GrooZo reserves the right to revoke offers in cases of misuse, fraud, or abuse.

9. User Conduct
  You agree NOT to:
  - Harass delivery partners or restaurant staff,
  - Misuse the cancellation or refund system,
  - Use the app for illegal activities,
  - Attempt to manipulate ratings or reviews,
  - Upload offensive or harmful content.
  - Violations may lead to account suspension or legal action.

10. Ratings & Reviews
  - Ratings and reviews must be genuine and based on actual experience.
  - GrooZo may moderate or remove reviews that are false, abusive, or misleading.

11. Intellectual Property
  All rights related to:
   - GrooZo name, logo, design, App UI, features, and underlying technology, are owned by GrooZo.
   - You may not copy, modify, or distribute any part of the App without written permission.

12. Limitation of Liability
  GrooZo is not liable for:
    Food quality or restaurant service,
  - Delays caused by external factors,
  - Incorrect addresses provided by users,
  - Losses arising from third-party actions (restaurants/delivery partners).
  - While we strive for the best service, GrooZo provides the platform “as is” without guarantees.

13. Privacy & Data Usage
  Your personal information is handled as per the GrooZo Privacy Policy, which includes:
  - Collection of contact details, order history, and delivery locations.
  - Sharing data with restaurants and delivery partners only for fulfilling orders.
  - GrooZo does not sell user data to third-party advertisers.

14. Suspension or Termination
  GrooZo may suspend or terminate your account for:
  - Fraudulent activity,
  - Abusive behavior,
  - Breach of these Terms,
  - Law enforcement requirements.

15. Governing Law
